# Trivy ignore file — accepted/suppressed findings.
# Docs: https://trivy.dev/docs/configuration/filtering/#by-finding-ids
#
# One ID per line (CVE-…, GHSA-…, AVD-… misconfig IDs, or secret rule IDs).
# Add an `# expires:` / rationale comment so suppressions are reviewable and
# don't become permanent blind spots.
#
# NOTE: dependency / vendored trees (node_modules, _bmad*, .worktrees) are
# excluded via `skip-dirs` in .github/workflows/security.yml rather than by
# listing their CVEs here — that keeps this file scoped to deliberate,
# our-code suppressions only.
#
# Example:
#   # Accepted 2026-06-03: transitive, dev-only, not shipped in the npm
#   #   tarball (package.json "files" ships bin/ lib/ _Sprintpilot/ only).
#   #   Re-evaluate when <pkg> releases a fix.
#   CVE-0000-00000

# (no accepted findings — root + tests lockfiles scan clean)
